# Notes App — Project Rules

## What this is
A v1 notes web app: users sign up / log in, then create and view their own private notes.
Requirements live in docs/stories/, decisions in docs/adr/, design in docs/design/.

## Stack (decided in ADR-001 — do not change without a new ADR)
- Frontend: Angular 18 SPA (src/notes-app-web)
- Backend: ASP.NET 8 Web API (src/NotesApp.Api)
- Data: EF Core + SQLite
- Auth: ASP.NET Core Identity, cookie-based

## Stack-specific setup
- EF migrations need the global tool (`dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef`) and the packages
  `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite` and `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design`.
- Identity: set `RequireConfirmedAccount = false` and `RequireConfirmedEmail = false`
  (email verification is out of scope; otherwise sign-in after register fails silently).

## Dev cross-origin config (avoids the "always 401")
- Angular dev origin is http://localhost:4200; the API runs over HTTPS in dev.
- CORS: `WithOrigins("http://localhost:4200")` + `AllowCredentials()`.
- Auth cookie: HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax, Secure in production. Angular calls use `withCredentials: true`.

## Hard boundaries (every agent, every request)
- Never accept UserId from the client; always derive it from the authenticated session/claims.
- Don't add features beyond docs/stories/ (no edit/delete, search, password reset, OAuth, etc.).

## Testing
- Automated tests live in a dedicated test project; set it up before writing integration tests,
  or label that verification manual.